
BYBIT_API_KEY / BYBIT_API_SECRET

1. Go to bybit.com, sign in to your account, click your avatar in the top-right corner, then open API (or go directly to "https://www.bybit.com/app/user/api-management").
2. Click Create New Key and choose System-generated API Keys (not Connect to Third-Party App).
3. Enable only the permissions the bot actually needs:
   - Contract → Orders: Read-Write
   - Contract → Positions: Read-Write
   - Leave everything else disabled, especially Withdrawal permissions. A trading bot should never have access to withdrawals.
4. It is strongly recommended to bind the API key to the IP address of the server running the bot. This makes the key useless if it ever leaks.
5. Bybit will show the API Key and API Secret only once. The secret cannot be viewed again later. If you lose it, you'll need to create a new key.

→ "BYBIT_API_KEY" = your API Key
→ "BYBIT_API_SECRET" = your API Secret

Testnet setup (recommended for your first run)

- Use the separate website: "https://testnet.bybit.com" (testnet accounts are separate from production accounts).
- Create API keys in API Management exactly the same way as on the main platform.
- Set "BYBIT_TESTNET=true" in your ".env" file. The bot will then connect to "api-testnet.bybit.com" and use your testnet credentials.
- You can request fake USDT/USDC from the built-in faucet and test real order placement without risking actual funds.

